    \caption{Color. (a) Differential conductance $dI/dV_{sd}$ in the normal state as a function of $V_{sd}$ at half-filling of six different diamonds: A (S-Al) and C, E, I, J and K (S-NbAl). (b) Temperature dependence of the same quantity, for ridges A (S-Al) and C (S-NbAl). To destroy the superconductivity in the contacts, a magnetic field is applied perpendicular to the sample: $B=0.13\mathrm{~T}$ for the diamond A and $B=1\mathrm{~T}$ for the diamonds C, E, I, J and K. }
    \label{dependence}
